      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Pseudoephedrine, the active ingredient in Sudafed, can sometimes be used cautiously during pregnancy, but it is not always recommended. It can raise blood pressure, which is something you should monitor closely. Before taking any decongestant, even an over-the-counter one, please call your doctor's office for immediate advice. They can confirm if it is safe for your specific stage of pregnancy.",
